ğŸ”¥ What Is Red Teaming?
Red Teaming is a full-scope, simulated cyberattack designed to test how well an organization can detect, respond to, and defend against real-world threats. Unlike traditional penetration testing (which is often technical and short-term), red teaming is more strategic and stealthyâ€”mimicking actual adversaries.

Think of the red team as the "ethical attackers" trying to break in, while the blue team (the client's security) tries to stop them.

ğŸ§  Purpose of Red Teaming
Test detection and response, not just vulnerabilities.

Simulate Advanced Persistent Threats (APTs)â€”like real-world hackers.

Go beyond tools and test people, processes, and technology.

ğŸ§© How You Can Offer Red Teaming Services
ğŸš© 1. Scoping & Planning
Start with defining:

The goals (e.g., test SOC effectiveness, bypass MFA, reach crown jewels).

Rules of Engagement (ROE): Whatâ€™s off-limits? Are blue teams aware?

Testing window and stealth level (noisy or covert?).

ğŸ§¾ Deliverable: Red Team Plan & ROE document

ğŸ§¨ 2. Reconnaissance (OSINT)
Gather intel on the targetâ€”like a real hacker would.

âœ… You Collect:
Employee names (LinkedIn, social media)

Email formats (for phishing)

